# ZenUI - AI Implementation Prompts
## How to Use AI to Build This Project

---

## 📋 Overview

This guide contains ready-to-use prompts for AI assistants (Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini, Copilot, etc.) to build ZenUI step by step.

---

## 🎯 Strategy: How to Work with AI

### Best Practices

1. **Work in phases** - Don't try to build everything at once
2. **One task at a time** - Give focused, specific prompts
3. **Share context** - Paste relevant sections of the PDR
4. **Iterate** - Review output, ask for refinements
5. **Test as you go** - Verify each component works before moving on

### Prompt Structure

```
[CONTEXT]
Brief background about the project

[TASK]
Specific thing you want the AI to do

[REQUIREMENTS]
Technical specifications and constraints

[OUTPUT]
What format you want the response in
```

---

## 🚀 Phase 1: Project Setup

### Prompt 1.1: Initialize Monorepo

```
I'm building a UI component library called "ZenUI" - similar to shadcn/ui but with glassmorphic components as the key differentiator.

Help me set up a pnpm monorepo with Turborepo.

Requirements:
- pnpm workspace with packages/ and apps/ directories
- Turborepo for build orchestration
- TypeScript 5.0+ with strict mode
- ESLint + Prettier configuration

Create these files:
1. package.json (root)
2. pnpm-workspace.yaml
3. turbo.json
4. tsconfig.json (base)
5. .eslintrc.js
6. .prettierrc

Use latest stable versions of all dependencies.
```

### Prompt 1.2: Create Core Package

```
Create the @zenui/core package for my UI library monorepo.

This package contains shared utilities used by all framework-specific packages.

Create these files in packages/core/:

1. package.json - with tsup for building, exports for ESM/CJS
2. tsconfig.json
3. src/utils/cn.ts - className merge utility using clsx + tailwind-merge
4. src/constants/design-tokens.ts - design tokens for glassmorphism:
   - Glass blur levels (sm: 8px, md: 12px, lg: 16px, xl: 24px)
   - Glass background colors (light/dark mode)
   - Glass border colors
   - Glass shadows (multi-layer for depth)
   - Animation durations and easing functions
5. src/types/index.ts - shared TypeScript types
6. src/index.ts - main export file

Use TypeScript with strict mode.
```

### Prompt 1.3: Create React Package Structure

```
Create the @zenui/react package structure for my UI library.

Requirements:
- TypeScript with strict mode
- tsup for building (ESM + CJS output)
- Peer dependencies: react 18+, react-dom 18+
- Dependencies: @zenui/core (workspace), class-variance-authority
- Folder structure for components organized by category

Create:
1. packages/react/package.json
2. packages/react/tsconfig.json
3. packages/react/src/index.ts
4. packages/react/src/components/glassmorphic/index.ts

The glassmorphic folder will contain our priority components.
```

---

## 🎨 Phase 2: Glassmorphic Components

### Prompt 2.1: Glass Card Component

```
Create a GlassCard component for my React UI library (@zenui/react).

Design specifications:
- Frosted glass effect with backdrop-blur
- Multiple variants: default, bordered, gradient, glow
- Blur intensity options: sm, md, lg, xl
- Size options: sm, md, lg, xl (affects padding)
- Optional "animated" prop for hover scale effect
- Optional "shine" prop for hover shine animation

Technical requirements:
- Use class-variance-authority (cva) for variant management
- Use the cn() utility from @zenui/core for class merging
- Use Tailwind CSS classes only
- Forward ref properly with React.forwardRef
- Full TypeScript types exported
- Accessible (proper ARIA if needed)

CSS values for glass effect:
- Background: bg-white/5 (dark mode)
- Border: border-white/10
- Blur: backdrop-blur-lg (16px default)
- Shadow: shadow-lg or custom glow shadow
- Hover: increase opacity slightly

Create:
1. packages/react/src/components/glassmorphic/glass-card/glass-card.tsx
2. packages/react/src/components/glassmorphic/glass-card/index.ts

Include JSDoc comments and usage examples in comments.
```

### Prompt 2.2: Glass Button Component

```
Create a GlassButton component for my React UI library.

Design specifications:
- Glass/frosted button with backdrop blur
- Variants: default, primary, success, danger, ghost
- Sizes: sm, md, lg, xl, icon
- Optional "glow" prop for hover glow effect
- Optional "magnetic" prop for cursor-following effect
- Loading state with spinner
- Support for left/right icons

Technical requirements:
- Use cva for variants
- Use cn() from @zenui/core
- Tailwind CSS only
- React.forwardRef
- Full TypeScript types
- Accessible: proper focus states, aria-disabled when loading

Styling:
- Base: backdrop-blur-md, border-white/20, rounded-xl
- Focus: visible ring with offset
- Active: scale-[0.98] for press feedback
- Disabled: opacity-50, pointer-events-none

Create the component file with all features implemented.
```

### Prompt 2.3: Glass Input Component

```
Create a GlassInput component for my React UI library.

Design specifications:
- Glass/frosted input field with backdrop blur
- Floating label that animates on focus
- Variants: default, filled, underline
- States: default, focus, error, success, disabled
- Support for left/right icons/addons
- Optional character count

Technical requirements:
- Use cva for variants
- Tailwind CSS only
- Proper accessibility: labels, aria-invalid, aria-describedby
- Controlled and uncontrolled modes
- Forward ref to the actual input element

Styling:
- Background: bg-white/5
- Border: border-white/10, focus:border-white/30
- Focus: ring effect with glow
- Placeholder: text-white/40
- Label: animate from inside to top on focus

Create the complete component with TypeScript types.
```

### Prompt 2.4: Glass Modal Component

```
Create a GlassModal component for my React UI library.

Design specifications:
- Glassmorphic modal dialog with frosted background
- Backdrop with blur effect
- Sizes: sm, md, lg, xl, full
- Smooth open/close animations (fade + scale)
- Close on overlay click (optional)
- Close on Escape key

Technical requirements:
- Use React Portal (createPortal)
- Focus trap when open
- Scroll lock on body when open
- Proper accessibility: role="dialog", aria-modal, aria-labelledby
- Return focus to trigger element on close
- Compound component pattern: Modal, Modal.Trigger, Modal.Content, Modal.Header, Modal.Footer

Styling:
- Overlay: bg-black/60, backdrop-blur-sm
- Content: glass card styling with glow variant
- Animations: animate-in, fade-in, zoom-in-95

Create the complete component with all features.
```

### Prompt 2.5: Remaining Glassmorphic Components

Use similar prompts for:
- Glass Navigation (navbar with glass effect)
- Glass Sidebar (side panel with glass)
- Glass Dropdown (dropdown menu with glass)
- Glass Panel (floating panel)

